Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.94,0:03:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.94,0:03:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going out for a training.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.86,0:03:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.35,0:03:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Late into the last night, Hiromi experienced it \Nfor the first time. Losing someone so important to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.70,0:03:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka, I'll be by your side until the end of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.93,0:03:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Meeting you was the grandest blessing of my life.{I think lit ver of "I'm happy to have met you." fits the mood better here, but I'm sticking to the phrasing from ep 5}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.29,0:04:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Jin, wake up. It's morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.55,0:04:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, Jin, \NI think I came up with a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.80,0:04:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Day after day, \NI will be thinking about Jin only.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.78,0:04:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,All the fun times, along with sad times...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.24,0:04:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't be doing anything else at all. \NJust drifting endlessly through my recollections of Jin.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.47,0:04:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,One year, two years, three years... \NAll of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.45,0:04:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Until I die!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.07,0:04:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.92,0:04:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.70,0:04:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm trembling in excitement.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.42,0:04:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I think if I don't act this way, \NI will hardly be happy ever again.{/ I think, if I act this way, I won't ever experience a greater happiness. / I think no greater happiness is possible than that of acting this way.}{i'm still doubtful about this line - both in translation and phrasing}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.42,0:05:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, at all times, \Nthis is the only thing the two of us cannot part with.{/ I see we both can't help holding on to this, whatever the times are.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.72,0:05:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,This teaching is deep-seated.{/ We were taught well.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.22,0:05:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You're through to Oka family.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.18,0:05:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Maki?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.39,0:05:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We are so grateful for your concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.55,0:05:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,How is Hiromi? About that...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.61,0:05:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Off for a training?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.03,0:05:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I swear, this girl Hiromi... \NIs she really that insensitive?{/ What kind of nerve does she have?}{I used the former phrasing for jikai part in last ep so I'm sticking with it now as well}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.98,0:06:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's call it a day here, Oka.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.64,0:06:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess, you too \Nwant to be left alone for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.74,0:06:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Left alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.64,0:06:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.87,0:06:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.40,0:06:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Howdy, howdy!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.99,0:06:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew you'd be here! \NBeen looking for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.28,0:06:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought because of jet lag, \Nyou'd still have a big head.{/hangover.}{/ you'd be still trying to get yourself together.}{it's a bit tricky one to rephrase: https://jisho.org/word/%E3%81%BC%E3%83%BC%E3%81%A3%E3%81%A8# - maybe "you'd still be sleepy"}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.39,0:06:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I'm told you're off for a training!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.77,0:06:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Old habits die hard, Maki.{/ A habit can be a terryfing thing, Maki.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.97,0:06:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if I don't have a mood for it, \Nmy body carries me to the training regardless.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.52,0:06:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It really does?{/ Is there really such a thing?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.51,0:06:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It does, does!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.16,0:06:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So, till tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.72,0:06:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.78,0:06:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,See you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.43,0:06:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Later!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.24,0:06:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I know! \NHey, Maki, how about we have fun{/Who don't we go out somewhere} today?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.42,0:07:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I was so-o-o preoccupied with this, \NI never got a day off to have fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.79,0:07:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So now I need a lot of fun to offset it!{/ I want to have fun thoroughly!}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.67,0:07:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,All right...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.61,0:07:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, at the hamburger shop \Nnext to the park at 10!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.13,0:07:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.76,0:07:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, time to change the attire{/dress up nicely}{I'm not really seeing what role the "mikka" part has, maybe "I'll have 3 days of dressing up" but Oka doesn't strike me like someone to say that} for once!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.78,0:07:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Later then. Bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.18,0:07:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.75,0:07:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.71,0:07:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back, Hiromi.\NHow was the training?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.74,0:07:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Refreshing to the heart and soul!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.70,0:07:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? That's a relief.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.07,0:07:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, I'm washing my face.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.18,0:07:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.59,0:07:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow, the mourning{Lit is "formal funerals" but I think mourning [ceremony] is effectively the same thing, just less confusing} for Mr. Munakata is held.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.56,0:07:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.32,0:08:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Friends are for times like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.38,0:08:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,While she is with me, I won't let a hint of sadness \Ninto Hiromi's mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.18,0:08:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,"Face is smiling while heart is crying."{/ Out of sight, out of mind.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.29,0:08:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,At any rate, I must engulf Hiromi in buoyancy, \Nmuch like a sea would.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.22,0:08:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Maki!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.57,0:08:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Kept you waiting{, huh}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.29,0:08:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.76,0:08:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, have you seen this? \NThis? Or this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.56,0:08:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,My, what a stadium jumper!{only part that I got for sure is "ジャン" in the end, which is some kind of jumper, but there's no such thing as "イカスジャン" so I shoehorned the usual スタジャン here; "kaaai" in the beginning - would assume it's just a meaningless exclamation and not "you bought"}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.10,0:08:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, that's right. \NStumbled upon this in New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.68,0:08:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Cool, cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.29,0:08:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't touched your hamburger yet? \NMind if I do?{guess, no idea what "manauyo" part is}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.46,0:08:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What's your deal, Hiromi? \NYou didn't get to eat your breakfast?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.14,0:08:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I've eaten in plenty, \Nbut for some unknown reason my stomach is growling.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.48,0:08:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Was planning to get full of authentic ones in America, \Nbut never got a day off.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.95,0:08:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Ended up returning to eating usual Japanese hamburgers \Nbefore a chance presented itself.{guess, this part after "tabete" is a scribble}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.07,0:09:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. That's right. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.72,0:09:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Wipe your tears. \NIt's unseemly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.46,0:09:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.50,0:09:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This way, it's unclear who is comforting{/ trying to distract} who. \NMaki, get yourself together!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.17,0:09:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh right, right. \NHey, Maki!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.01,0:09:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.46,0:09:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,How about amusement park? \NLet's party!{they use "pa-to" in this funny way all along this and next OVA, can't be helped I reckon}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.01,0:09:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I approve! Was thinking about that too. \NI approve the party!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.76,0:09:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.48,0:09:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.43,0:09:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Did it, you did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.43,0:09:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You little one!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.39,0:10:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This is perfect!{guess} So cool!{/Wonderful!}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.91,0:10:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach Munakata!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.21,0:10:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi, what did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.71,0:10:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi... Hey, what's wrong, Hiromi? Hiromi!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.18,0:11:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, she has been like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.37,0:11:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you again for your concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.83,0:11:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, is that all?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.58,0:11:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand. Thanks for your time, \NI won't bother you more.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.50,0:11:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What did they tell you?{half-guess after "donna"}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.47,0:11:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,After she returned from her "jaunt for fun," \Nthey never heard a word from her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.55,0:11:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Just rushed into her room \Nand never came out even for a meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.98,0:11:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess, it's no use calling her out after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.84,0:11:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.27,0:11:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go there with just four of us.{/Let's visit this place with us only.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.94,0:11:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry for intrusion. \NWe are Nishi High graduates.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.94,0:11:42.82,Sign,,0,0,0,,Munakata
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.42,0:11:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We are really sorry to have come unannounced.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.95,0:12:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But we absolutely needed to present Coach \Nwith homecoming report before the mourning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.96,0:12:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no. It's good you decided to pay us a visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.10,0:12:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Jin would no doubt had been happy with it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.04,0:12:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You probably never heard of it, \Nbut our daughter got married when she was 18{I hear 18 but I don't recognize the word after it, most likely it's "nen to" - "y.o. and" which is again not exactly "at ... y.o." but I'm ovethinking again, most likely}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.74,0:12:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,A few years later, she returned to this house, \Ncarrying baby Jin.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.78,0:12:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But before long,{/ soon after,} she fell ill and perished.{/ withered away.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.46,0:12:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, our sweet grandson Jin also followed her, \Noutrunning us both.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.95,0:12:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we're just an aged pair, \Nleft alone in this big house.{a wild guess, but it may also mean (unlikely though) "The two people we brought up both left us alone in this spacious house.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.02,0:12:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet even so, we can keep on living.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.29,0:12:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we have hope, \Nwe can move on from today to tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.98,0:12:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, we now have Daigo here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.98,0:12:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We have all of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.03,0:12:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a player named Oka Hiromi!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.42,0:12:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What Jin left behind...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.97,0:12:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The product of life Jin's spent in this house{really unsure about "this house" part, it looks a bit out of place} \Nis this spectacular linkage of souls he left behind!{/What Jin managed to leave behind in the house he lived his life in is this spectacular unity/connection of souls.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.18,0:12:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It encourages us to live on.{I invented this "to live on" to make this sentence look complete}{/It makes us tremble in awe.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.54,0:12:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Compared to my 84 years long life, Jin's life of 27 years \Nis in no way inferior, but in many aspects, surpasses it!{/ Jin's 27 years of life can rival and even surpass my 84 years of life.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.39,0:13:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,However, in those 27 years, \Nthat flew by in a blink of an eye,{/like one instant,}{been sitting on this "ya" for 6 hours, still no clue what this means, the closest I can get is "home" and accordingly "those 27 that flew by in this house" which is logically and grammatically incorrect - it translates into "flew away in the same way as that house" - methinks an obscure old japanese idiom is involved with this "ya" meaning something like a swift bird, so in this case even johnny's variant of "that were brief like a lightning" may do}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.14,0:13:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,even if for a short instant, even if for a split second, \Ndid he act like a spoiled child?{Lit is "that child spoiled people" but I don't see what it may mean, so would write it off to just "spoiled child"} Indulged himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.54,0:13:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Was negligent to details?{/Allowed himself trifling mishaps?}{it's the same word as 2 lines, but here it uses positive connotation as "small yet important minutae" and 2 lines later it's "small and unimportant trifles"} \NForgave{/Excused} himself anything of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.58,0:13:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Squandered the time away \Nin meaningless distractions?{/Lit: Let himself fool around good-for-nothing things to his heart's content?}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.33,0:13:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm talking about all those little trifles, \Neveryone cannot imagine his life without.{/Lit: For ordinary people, meaningless as they are, those things are so important.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.62,0:13:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, I can't help wondering \Nif there was ever an actual{not sure what "hatashite" means here, would assume it's "really"} moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.80,0:13:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,when he thought to himself \N"I'm so glad to be alive!"{/if he ever managed to have a moment for himself to be glad of being alive.}{I hate that I had to give this sentence a johnny treatment by reversing it line-wise, but I don't see how to help it}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.29,0:13:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,This kid's 27 years that ran out so abruptly{/ that he rushed through way too hastily}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.44,0:13:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,will resound{unsure about "itakaseru" part, my closest guess is "to hurt" but that sounds redundant since "heartbreaking thoughts" already implies pain} with heartbreaking{/sorrowful} thoughts \Nin everything and everyone{Lit would be "things he left behind" but it's a bit too german to say that about people present; previously I tackled this with "What he left behind"} he left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.86,0:13:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll answer the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.45,0:13:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It must be on the matter \Nof tomorrow's mourning ceremony{ [arrangement]}.{strongly considering flipping back to literal "official funerals" at this point}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.87,0:13:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, Mr. Daigo goes to a lot of trouble \Nto look after{/ care for} us in place of Jin.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.30,0:14:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He hardly ever spills a single word about himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.70,0:14:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's something else \NI want you all to keep in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.08,0:14:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,While Jin and Daigo were rivals in tennis, \Nin usual life{guess; no clue about "denjin" part in the end} they were each other's one and only best friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.47,0:14:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That state of affairs remains unaltered even now, \Nwhen Jin is no more.{/And even the fact Jin is dead now does not change it one bit.}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.64,0:14:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Those two were both
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.52,0:14:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,knocked down by a sudden tragedy five years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.48,0:14:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Marrow{/Myeloid} leukemia.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.82,0:14:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And also quite advanced at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.43,0:14:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The diagnosis gave him \Nno more than 3 more years to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.94,0:14:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally, he retired from playing{/ active duty}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.26,0:14:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That kid, fortuneless ever since childhood, \Nhas been thrown further down the stairs.{/As luck would have it, this kid, unfavored since childhood, received a finishing blow.}{guess in the "hionda" part}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.04,0:14:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Truly, the God has not been tender in his mischief.{/I can't think of it as anything but a God's prank.}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.46,0:14:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet this kid managed to move on even from that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.17,0:14:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,When I made up my mind to become a coach,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.92,0:14:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Daigo and I made a promise between us:
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.55,0:14:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,When I come across a player worth putting my life{/heart and soul/worth investing my everything} into, \NDaigo would back me by nurturing this player further on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.71,0:15:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But immediately{no idea what this "chopu" is; sounds kinda like "choku" - direct / immediate, so I surmised that; also close to "chop" - a sharp sideways stroke in tennis that causes a lot of backspin or a hit with the edge of the hand in wrestling - can't see how any of that makes sense here} after that, Daigo's response actions{/reaction / demeanor} \Nhad everyone around them no less dumbfounded.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.52,0:15:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder -{/ After all,} that same day, \Nhe discarded{/abandoned} tennis and gone missing{/disappeared}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.14,0:15:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It was only later that we found out - as a {newly tonsured }monk \Npracticing {extreme }asceticism{/austerity}, he cloistered himself in Eihei{ji=buddhist temple} Temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.19,0:15:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Eihei Temple?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.49,0:15:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That school of Buddhism{he actually says temple again, but its oniyomi differs from previous sentense, so I replace it to sound more consistent}, \Nwith the most{/known for its} severe precepts{/austere practices}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.36,0:15:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, thanks for all your trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.97,0:15:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, Daigo never came down the mountain \Nfor three years.{a bit unsure about whole sentence; Lit would be "Daigo descended a mountain, since then 3 years passed already"}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.25,0:15:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it was the time \Nwhen I came across you, Oka.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.55,0:15:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Still buried in the ground{/covered by the soil/hidden in the earth/obscured/nameless}, \Nyour brilliance was not yet noticeable to a naked eye.{/your light/brightness/radiance was therefore unable to reach someone's eye.}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.68,0:15:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But I could see it, Oka - to me, you were unmistakably \Nthe most important thing ever, {this is actually a continuation of previous line, but I split that sentence}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.38,0:15:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,shining like the craziest{/beautiful/lovely} diamond already.{this is a stupid reference but I'd trust Munakata had a good taste in music}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.81,0:15:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the same for everyone.{/Everyone does that.}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.78,0:15:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Step by step, we use up \Nthe little time allotted to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.18,0:15:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you realize{/notice/are aware of} it or not.{unsure in both transcription and translation - 気付くは気付くまいが}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.22,0:15:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you focus on it{/pay attention/look closely at it} or not.{this one is more discernable but I'm still feeling buoyant; maybe he meant "Whether you're trying to escape it or not" idk}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.33,0:15:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The end is coming inevitably.{/With every day, you're going to your end.}{kakujitsu may mean both "certainly" and "every day", thus so different variants}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.74,0:16:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the real question is, in this allotted{he says "this limited" and not exactly alloted, not the same adjective as 4 lines before, but I'm trying to stay in the line here} time, what to look{/aim} for{/what is your purpose}, in what direction to step forward{/where to proceed}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.61,0:16:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We can but admire the lofty ideals \NCoach{he actually says "coaches" or "coach's party" but it'll be awkward to call Daigo one yet, as well as mentioning his name explicitly here} aligned himself with.{/What high ideals Coach put up for himself to aspire to!}{not really sure what "hotsu" part in the end stands for, probably just a meaningless appendix}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.23,0:16:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no telling if a player \Nworth betting his everything{"putting his life into" would sound more consistent with previous iterations of this phrase, yet life is used explicitly in the next line, unfortunately} on exists,{/No one could ever guarantee there is a player that deserves putting his life into,/devoting yourself to,}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.11,0:16:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,yet Coach Munakata put{/devoted ... to} his life \Ninto unearthing{trying to follow the analogy with "diamong buried in the earth" from earlier} one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.84,0:16:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,While Mr. Katsura put his life to ascetic practices, \Ncloistering himself in Eihei{ Temple} to safeguard best friend's will.{Lit: Katsura, in order to carry on his bosom friend's will, secluded himself to Eihei Temple to live a life of deprivations.}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.05,0:16:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What an overwhelming resolve.{"force of will" would fit better, but I already used that word in previous line}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.32,0:16:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet this ideal is still only half-achieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.11,0:16:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Since this player by the name of Oka Hiromi \Nproved to exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.40,0:16:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But the harsh reality{ now} is, \NCoach Munakata is no longer alive.{sounds a bit awkward but that's the best phrasing I could come up with to tie this up with the next line}{/Lit: But now, the reality has to face the fact of Coach Munakata's death.}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.28,0:16:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Truly harsh, merciless{/ A big, undeniable} and unwavering reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.24,0:16:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What now? Their ideal is still nowhere near \Nbeing achieved in reality.{/Lit: The guarantee of successful fullfillment of this ideal in reality is nowhere to be seen.}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.39,0:16:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I there anything we can do about it!?{Lit: What is it we should do now?}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.08,0:16:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.55,0:16:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll get drenched, Coach!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.85,0:17:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.52,0:17:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But it may harm your health{/ body}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.73,0:17:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't matter anymore. \NI'm completely free at last.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.70,0:17:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I can tell you no more than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.11,0:17:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But... Coach?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.11,0:17:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you going now?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.09,0:17:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,No more than that.{/I can't tell you more./I really told you enough.}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.74,0:17:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.59,0:17:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I will forever stay by your side.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.92,0:17:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Please wait! Coach!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.15,0:17:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Meeting you was the grandest blessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.71,0:17:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach... Please wait! Coach!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.64,0:17:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach! Coach!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.30,0:17:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, I have to be very careful \Nto not burst into tears before Hiromi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.98,0:18:08.50,Sign,,0,0,0,,Munakata Family Mourning Ceremony{ Venue}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.08,0:19:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord1}Hiromi. Hiromi, it's your turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.90,0:19:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach, look what I've got.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.07,0:19:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,This medal...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.78,0:19:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I won as a runner-up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.08,0:19:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,A word... Just one word... \NPlease tell me I've done well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.52,0:19:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{It's }So unfair!{/Mean/Dishonest!}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.78,0:19:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.82,0:20:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.60,0:20:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,About my work... \NI think I'll take a vacation for a week or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.14,0:20:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Even as parents, \Nwe can do little but watch her suffer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.02,0:20:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So why don't we take Hiromi \Nout on a little journey?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.61,0:20:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I was once just like you are{ now}.{/You remind me of my younger self.}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.07,0:21:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to forget many things.{/There were many things I wanted to forget.}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.02,0:21:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, I even forgot \Nmy body has a limited lifespan.{it's quite literal, but "my body has a limit" might sound more natural}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.12,0:21:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,However, this one ball \Nis never like any other{/ is definetely a unique} {one }ball.{I genuinely wonder if it's just a precept about usual tennis balls or some cryptic idiom for "life" like in johnny's ver}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.80,0:21:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you put your heart and soul \Ninto each smash{it's not actually smash but hearing this word on the same place in sub and in audio is appealing}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.88,0:21:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I only came to understanding those words with my heart\Nafter I had to cut short my tennis career.{/Those words began moving me to the core from the moment I was severed from my tennis career.}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.35,0:21:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Because just like it did, \Neverything has its end.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.13,0:21:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Be it a life or a match, \Nit has its end.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.28,0:21:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Day by day, day by day, ball by ball, \Nsteadily and invariably{basically, those are effectively "always and certainly" so any synonim would do}, that end draws closer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.70,0:21:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, mindful that this moment will never {really }come again, \Nyou{ must} put your life {unreservedly / fully }into it, and hit this {one }ball with all your might!{as you can see, I had to prune this line significantly to fit it into 2 lines and 20cps}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.36,0:21:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It was only later{/after it} that I realized,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.29,0:21:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka, while you can move freely, while you can run freely, \Nkeep playing without any second thoughts{/regrets}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.66,0:21:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But... But!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.79,0:21:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I can no longer play any tennis.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.14,0:21:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.12,0:23:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Aikawa Maki.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.68,0:23:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Madame Butterfly, Todo and everyone \Nare worrying really bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.26,0:23:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, Hiromi won't even come to eat, \Njust staring at the sea instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.67,0:23:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If she cannot even take food, \Nit's over for her!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.36,0:23:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, what should we do about Hiromi?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.13,0:23:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, though,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.54,0:23:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach Katsura suddenly offers to take Hiromi \Nunder his custody in the Temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.68,0:23:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Next episode: Into Sorrow
